{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Many bacterial species are capable of utilising agmatine (a decarboxylated derivative of arginine) as an energy source via the agamtine deiminase pathway. Agmatine deiminase converts agmatine to carbamoyl putrescine, which is subsequently phosphorylised to carbamoyl phosphate and putrescine by putrescine carbamoyltransferase [[cite:PUB00041924]]. The carbamoyl phosphate is used to generate ATP by phosphorylating ADP, while the putrescine is exchanged with extracellular agmatine by an agmatine/putrescine antiporter.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false} {"text" "<p>This entry represents the putrescine carbamoyltransferase from this pathway. It is closely related to the ornithine carbamoyltransferase involved in the analogous arginine utilisation pahtway.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "4am8", "name" "Crystal structure of the R54G mutant of putrescine transcarbamylase from Enterococcus faecalis bound to a curing guanidinium ion"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR036901", "name" "Aspartate/ornithine carbamoyltransferase superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"ncbifam" {"TIGR04384" "putrescine carbamoyltransferase"}, "hamap" {"MF_02102" "Putrescine carbamoyltransferase [ptcA]"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Putrescine carbamoyltransferase PtcA", "short" "PtcA"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 5, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 116, "taxa" 684, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 535, "sets" 0, "proteins" 535, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 438}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"ec" {"displayName" "ENZYME", "description" "ENZYME is a repository of information relative to the nomenclature of enzymes. It is primarily based on the recommendations of the Nomenclature Committee of the International Union of Bio